Stress
=-=-=-=
Myth: People Should try to avoid all situations that can 
lead to stress.

Fact: Stress is a normal part of life that you cannot
avoid. Sometimes stress can have a positive outcome.

++Definitions++
Stress
 Stress is the Responce of your body and mind to 
 being challenged or threatened.

Stressor
 An even or situation that caused stress is called a
 Stressor

Four General types of stressors are
major life changes
-Graduating From highschool
-Being accepted to collage
-Breaking up with a boyfreind/girlfreind

catastraphes
-A catastaphe is an event that threatenes lives and 
 may destroy property

everyday problems
-SOme of the most common stressors are minor
 but freqent everyday events.

-Conflics dissagreements may be another causer of

enviromental problems
-Conditions in your immedate sourrounding affect
 your level of stress each day

-A major stressor that occurs all around you but is
 often overlooked is noise

-Living in unsafe or croided condidions 
 increse to stressfull living conditions

Stages of stress
The Body's Response to stress occurs in three stages
-The alarm stage
-The resistance stage
-The Exhaustion stage

Flight or fight Stages
-adrenaline 
 Raises you heart Blood pressure and increases 
 Oxegin to your brain.
-Releases sugar to your blod
-Blood flow decreases in your skin
-Flow of blood to degestive system reduced.
 Digestion slows more Stomach acid Produces
-Pupils open wide.
-Muscles tense more energey
-Lump in your throat

Resistance Stage
-During this stage, your body adapts to the continued
 Presence of Stress

Exhaustion Stage
-Your Body can no longer keep up with the demands
 placed on it

-YOur physical and emotional resources are depleated

-Exhaustion occurs only if a stressor continures for a 
 long time-Usually weeks, months, or even years.

Physical Changes
-Muscle tension
-Headache
-Upset stomach
-Pounding heart
-Shortness of breath
-Increased sweating
-skin rash

Emotional Changes
-Irritable
-Angry
-Impatient
-Nervous
-Increased Crying

Changes is Thinking
-Unable to COncentrate
-Negitive Thinking
-Excessive worrying
-Self Critsism
-Critical of others

Behavoral Changes
-OverEating or Hardly eating at all
-Sleep problems
-Hurrying; Talking fast
-Withdraw from relationships
-Reckless behavior

Stress or illness
Stress can triggger certain illnesses
-Stomacheaches
-Asthma
-Headaches
-Lowered Resistance to Disease
-Heart Disease




